Cape Town - Police are investigating a case of culpable homicide after the death of a man and a child in a car crash in Wetton. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said a man and a child were killed and two others injured when their car crashed into a wall and rolled at the Wetton and Rosmead intersection on Wednesday evening. “ER24, Metro Rescue, Western Cape Fire and other services arrived at 7.25pm to find a wrecked light motor vehicle upright on the centre median. A man was found lying trapped in the rear of the car while another man and two boys, believed to be 8 and 9 years old, were found seated outside,” Meiring said in a statement. Medics found that the man inside the vehicle had already died, and one boy died in spite of advanced life support interventions. Police spokesperson Frederick van Wyk confirmed a culpable homicide case was opened by Wynberg Police. “A 19-year-old man and 9-year-old child were fatally injured and the other occupants were taken to a nearby hospital for medcal treatment,” Van Wyk said. Anyone with information can call Crime Stop on 08600 10111. shakirah.thebus@inl.co.za Cape Argus